Samizdat is a Mojolicious-based static-content hybrid generator that prioritises
speed, internationalisation and offline capability. Content is authored in Markdown
and YAML and rendered to static HTML and WebP. It ships a back-office hosting panel
and integrates with external services through optional Samizdat-Plugin-* modules.

This port installs the core application and its rc.d service scripts (samizdat,
minion). Configuration lives under ${PREFIX}/etc/samizdat/, per-site content and the
generated static cache under /usr/local/www/samizdat/.
